  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1 \u0dbb\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0d9a\u0da7 \u0d9c\u0dd2\u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dad \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Thunderstorms at many places",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Department of Meteorology says that due to the development of a lower atmospheric disturbance in Sri Lanka, there will be occasional rain or thundershowers in many areas.",
        "Accordingly, on today (31), some places in the Western, Southern, Sabaragamuwa, Central and Uva provinces will experience very heavy rains of more than 150 millimeters and some places in other provinces will experience heavy rains of more than 100 millimeters, said a spokesperson of the department.",
        "The spokesman also mentioned that the sky in the southern half of the island is heavy with clouds.",
        "The Department of Meteorology advises people to take action to avoid accidents as lightning accidents and temporary strong winds are also possible along with thunderstorms.",
        "(Diana Udayangani) The Department of Meteorology says that due to the development of a lower atmospheric disturbance over Sri Lanka, there will be occasional rain or thundershowers in many areas. Accordingly, on today (31), some places in the Western, Southern, Sabaragamuwa, Central and Uva provinces will experience very heavy rains of more than 150 millimeters and some places in other provinces will experience heavy rains of more than 100 millimeters, said a spokesperson of the department. The spokesman also mentioned that the sky in the southern half of the island is heavy with clouds. The Department of Meteorology advises people to take action to avoid accidents as lightning accidents and temporary strong winds are also possible along with thunderstorms."
      ],
